def pickle_load(file):
    with open(file, 'rb') as f:
        print(f'file {file} loaded')
        return pickle.load(f)

def gzip_pickle_save(x, file):
    with gzip.open(file, 'wb') as f:
        pickle.dump(x, f)
    print(f'file {file} written')

    # get full sequence of cassette
    s = cassette['forward_start']
    e = cassette['reverse_end']
    return str(minicircles[cassette['mO_name']].seq)[s:e]

cassettes['sequence'] = cassettes.apply(get_cas_seq, args=(minicircles,), axis=1)

# this is very slow so results are pickled
def u_tail_len(non_coding_3p_seq, non_coding_5p_seq, strand):
    lengths = pd.Series([0 for _ in range(len(strand))])
    mask = (strand == 'coding')
    lengths[mask] = non_coding_3p_seq.str.len()
    mask = (strand == 'template')
    lengths[mask] = non_coding_5p_seq.str.len()
    return lengths

init_site_range = config['initiation site range']
fit_range = config['transcript position fit range']

# use cassette-associated transcripts outside of initiation site 
# to minimise effect of expressed gRNAs on coding strand
mask2 = transcripts['cassette_label'] != 'Orphan'
cas_transcripts = transcripts[mask2]

# count number of transcripts at each position from forward repeat
distributions = cas_transcripts.groupby(['strand', 'rel_pos'])['mO_name'].count()

def plot(distributions, strand, axes, scale, colour='C0', rescale=1):
    ss = slice(fit_range[0], fit_range[1])
    distribution = distributions[strand]
    x = distribution.index[ss]

    if scale == 'linear':
        axes.bar(x, distribution.values[ss]*rescale, color=colour, label='data')
    else:
        axes.bar(x, np.log10(distribution.values[ss]), color=colour, label='data')

    if strand == 'coding':
        axes.set_xlabel('Sense-strand transcript position relative to forward 18 bp repeat')
    else:
        axes.set_xlabel('Anti-sense strand transcript position relative to reverse 18 bp repeat')
        
    if scale == 'linear' and strand == 'coding':
        if rescale == 1:
            axes.set_ylabel('Number of sense strand transcripts')  
        else:
            axes.set_ylabel('Number of sense strand transcripts (x$10^6$)')  
    elif scale == 'log' and strand == 'coding':
        axes.set_ylabel('$Log_{10}$ number of sense strand transcripts')   
    elif scale == 'linear' and strand == 'template':
        axes.set_ylabel('Number of anti-sense strand transcripts')   
    elif scale == 'log' and strand == 'template':
        axes.set_ylabel('$Log_{10}$ number of anti-sense strand transcripts')   
        
def fit(transcripts, strand, init_site_range, axes):
    print(strand)
    transcripts = transcripts.query('strand == @strand')
    mask = (init_site_range[0] <= transcripts['rel_pos']) & (transcripts['rel_pos'] <= init_site_range[1])
    transcripts = transcripts[~mask]
    print(f'number outside of init site = {len(transcripts)}')
    mu = transcripts["rel_pos"].mean()
    sigma = transcripts["rel_pos"].std()
    p = norm.cdf(33, mu, sigma)-norm.cdf(30, mu, sigma)
    print(f'mean = {mu:.1f}')
    print(f'std = {sigma:.1f}')
    print(f'p = {p:.3f}')
    distribution = transcripts.groupby(['rel_pos'])['mO_name'].count()
    init_length = init_site_range[1] - init_site_range[0] + 1
    ss = slice(fit_range[0], fit_range[1]-init_length)
    x = distribution.index[ss]
    y = np.log10(distribution.values[ss])
    z = np.polyfit(x, y, 2)
    f = np.poly1d(z)
    sigma = np.sqrt(-np.log10(np.exp(1))/(2*z[0]))
    mu = -z[1]/(2*z[0])
    p = norm.cdf(33, mu, sigma)-norm.cdf(30, mu, sigma)
    print(f'mu = {mu:.1f}')
    print(f'sigma = {sigma:.1f}')
    print(f'p = {p:.3f}')
    axes.plot(x, f(x), color='g', label='fit')
    axes.set_ylim(0, 6.7)
    axes.legend()

def ngRNAs(gRNAs):
    if len(gRNAs) == 2:
        if ('_v' in gRNAs.iloc[0]['mRNA_name'] and '_v' in gRNAs.iloc[1]['mRNA_name']
         and gRNAs.iloc[0]['product'] == gRNAs.iloc[0]['product']):
            return 1
    return len(gRNAs)

def matches(cassette):
    match = {'AT':1, 'TA':1, 'GC':1, 'CG':1, 'GT':1, 'TG':1}
    return sum([1 if f+r in match else 0 for f, r in zip(cassette['forward_seq'], cassette['reverse_seq'][::-1])])

#matching between the same cassette pairs
cassettes['matches'] = cassettes.apply(matches, axis=1)
print(cassettes['matches'].describe())

#matching between random cassettes
random_cas = deepcopy(cassettes[['forward_seq', 'reverse_seq']])
random_cas['reverse_seq'] = random_cas['reverse_seq'].sample(frac=1).reset_index(drop=True)
random_cas['matches'] = random_cas.apply(matches, axis=1)
print(random_cas['matches'].describe())

def calculate_biases(group, length):
    # set up matrices of nucleotide frequencies along sequences
    count = {i: Counter() for i in range(length)}
    for seq in group.values:
        for i, b in enumerate(seq):
            count[i][b] += 1

    for i in range(len(count)):
        total = sum(count[i].values())
        for b in 'ACGT':
            count[i][b] /= total
    return pd.DataFrame.from_dict(count, orient='index')

def get_seq(c, start, length):
    s = int(c['rel_start'])+18+start
    return c['sequence'][s:s+length]

def get_ne_seq(c, start, length):
    s = 30+18+start
    return c['sequence'][s:s+length]

Frequency of ATA, AAA and ACA in initiation sequences¶

def get_init_seq3(c):
    #seqs = ('ATA','AAA','ACA')
    seqs=('ACA','D')
    if c['expression'] == 'non-expressed':
        # if gRNA is not expressed test if ATA AAA ot ACA occur
        # from position 30 to 32
        seq = c['sequence'][47:47+7][:3]
        return any([i in seq for i in seqs])
    else:
        # gRNA is expressed, test if ATA AAA or ACA occur at start of
        # initiation seq
        try:
            return any([i == c['init_seq'][:3] for i in seqs])
        except:
            return False

def remove_title(axes, text):
    """remove title pandas adds to groupedby boxplots"""
    for i in axes.get_children():
        if isinstance(i, plt.Text) and i.get_text() == text:
            i.set_text('')
            return
rel_pos = 0
anchor_regex = re.compile(r'\|{6,}')

def get_length(pairing):
    m = anchor_regex.search(pairing[::-1])
    if m == None:
        return None
    else:
        return len(m.group(0))

Coverage stats (table S3)¶

In [32]:
min_anchor_length = 6

columns = [
    'product',
    'total gRNAs',
    'missing gRNAs',
    'insertions',
    'insertions covered',
    'insertions not covered',
    'deletions',
    'deletions covered',
    'deletions not covered'
    ]
df_data = OrderedDict([(c, []) for c in columns])

for mRNA_name, mRNA_record in sorted(mRNAs.items()):
    if mRNA_name == 'COX2':
        continue
    gRNA_records = gRNAs_all.query('mRNA_name == @mRNA_name')
    mRNA_seq = mRNA_record['seq']
    gRNA_exists = np.zeros(len(mRNA_seq))
    no_gRNAs = 0

    for _, gRNA in gRNA_records.iterrows():
        no_gRNAs += 1

        start = gRNA['mRNA_start']
        end   = gRNA['mRNA_end']-min_anchor_length
        gRNA_exists[start:end] += 1

    insertions    = np.array(list(mRNA_seq)) == 'u'
    insert_exists = [i and (g>0) for i, g in zip(insertions, gRNA_exists) if i]
    deletions     = [0 if i == '-' else int(i) for i in mRNA_record['deletions']]

    x, no_missing = 0, 0
    while x < len(mRNA_seq):
        if (insertions[::-1][x] or deletions[::-1][x]) and not gRNA_exists[::-1][x]:
            x += 40-min_anchor_length
            no_missing += 1
        else:
            x += 1

    df_data['product'].append(mRNA_name)
    df_data['total gRNAs'].append(no_gRNAs)
    df_data['missing gRNAs'].append(no_missing)
    df_data['insertions'].append(len(insert_exists))
    df_data['insertions covered'].append(insert_exists.count(True))
    df_data['insertions not covered'].append(insert_exists.count(False))
    df_data['deletions'].append(sum(deletions))
    df_data['deletions covered'].append(sum([i for i, g in zip(deletions, gRNA_exists) if i and (g>0) ]))
    df_data['deletions not covered'].append(sum([i for i, g in zip(deletions, gRNA_exists) if i and (g==0) ]))
df = pd.DataFrame(df_data)

total = df.apply(np.sum)
total['product'] = 'total'
df = df.append(pd.DataFrame(total.values, index=total.keys()).T, ignore_index=True)

df.to_excel(f'{tables_dir}/coverage_{date}.xlsx')

print(df.to_string(index=False))

# count number of transcripts at each position from forward repeat

def plot(transcripts, strand, axes, colour='C0', rescale=1, fit=False):
    transcripts = transcripts.query('strand == @strand')
    distribution = transcripts.groupby('rel_pos')['mO_name'].count()
    ss = slice(fit_range[0], fit_range[1])
    x = distribution.index[ss]
#     x = distribution.index
    axes.bar(x, distribution[ss].values*rescale, color=colour, label='data')
    
    if fit:
        n = len(transcripts)
        mu = transcripts["rel_pos"].mean()
        sigma = transcripts["rel_pos"].std()
        p = norm.cdf(33, mu, sigma)-norm.cdf(30, mu, sigma)
        print(f'number outside of init site = {n}')
        print(f'mean = {mu:.1f}')
        print(f'std = {sigma:.1f}')
        print(f'p = {p:.3f}')

        axes.plot(x, n*norm.pdf(x, mu, sigma))

    if strand == 'coding':
        axes.set_xlabel('Sense-strand transcript position\ndownstream from forward 18 bp repeat')
        if rescale == 1:
            axes.set_ylabel('Number of sense strand transcripts')  
        else:
            axes.set_ylabel('Number of sense strand transcripts (x$10^6$)')  
    else:
        axes.set_xlabel('Anti-sense strand transcript position\nupstream from reverse 18 bp repeat')
        axes.set_ylabel('Number of anti-sense strand transcripts')
